A WOMAN who knifed her husband to death has been jailed for six months for driving down a motorway in the wrong direction. Killer drove wrong way on motorway A WOMAN who knifed her husband to death has been jailed for six months for driving down a motorway in the wrong direction.Former teacher Madge Gillespie, 65, was seen crashing into a barrier before driving on to the motorway.Gillespie, from Giffnock, who was jailed for killing her husband Thomas Boyle in 2004, admitted dangerous driving and drink driving at Glasgow Sheriff Court.She was jailed for six months. 